manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: F145: Rockland Melbourne Hardside Expandable Spinner Wheel Luggage This carry on is made of ABS. This material is extremely lightweight, durable, and protects the contents of your luggage. Multi-directional double spinner wheels rotate 360 degrees for easy maneuverability. This luggage allows you to pack more while avoiding the excess weight surcharges imposed by most airlines. 22"x13. 5"x9" (with wheels)

Features and Design Telescoping Handle The telescoping handle stows away conveniently and allows for easy maneuvering when extended. Expandable The upright expands an extra 2 inches in depth to maximize your packing capacity. Double Spinner Wheels Double spinner wheels allow for durable 360 degree maneuverability wherever your travels take you.

About Rockland Luggage Since its inception in 1998, Rockland by Fox Luggage has been proudly producing quality luggage and bags for the style savvy traveler. Recognized for its graphic and colorful designs, Rockland prides itself on creating products influenced by current trends in design and fashion. Our products turn heads in a crowd and stand out in the baggage carousel, making it easy for quick exits out the airport. Affordable and travel resistant, Rockland bags are an ideal companion for everything from quick trips to the gym to overnight getaways to extended vacations. Our selection includes: luggage sets (4 piece, 3 piece or 2 piece), hard cases, soft cases, carry ons, rolling backpacks, travel duffels, rolling duffels, cosmetic bags, and kids' backpacks. Over the years, a few Rockland products have been featured in film and television. Their colorful designs make them ideal for an eye catching visual element on screen.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars So cute and light and holds a lot!
reviews.reviewText: I love this little bag. Great for weekend trips. The wheels seem sturdy, I dragged it all over downtown NYC. Worked well. Cute colors too!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Beyond my expectations
reviews.reviewText: Let me tell you about this little YET BIG carry-on luggage. I have trucked it to at least four different locations one of them, including Europe I packed 10 days worth of clothing. Granted it was summer, so I didn’t need any heavy items and it is light. It is wonderful and I can’t rave enough about it that I ended up buying three more for my entire family. We trucked it all around Europe on the cobblestone streets and I can’t believe the wheels withstood all of the running around we did with them. Super durable can’t believe the great price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Really good, especially for the price
reviews.reviewText: I’m pretty snobby about luggage. My own personal luggage is the reliable high end stuff. But my newborn needed her own carry on for a trip to Miami and I wasn’t willing to buy her real luggage yet. This works great. Very very lightweight, rolls well, and held a ton of baby gear that we didn’t want to risk checking in a bag. This thing rolled all over Miami airport with no problems. The lining fabric is a little thin and might rip fast, but it has not yet. Can’t believe how affordable this piece is!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 29, 2023
reviews.reviewText: First, let me start by saying I found the 28" version of this suitcase at Goodwill for $8!! It was in amazing like new condition. Although, it was not a color I normally would have picked, the price dictated the purchase. I didn't know anything about Rockland luggage at the time. I was just impressed with the suitcase. It's hard-sided, yet lightweight and also has ample room inside. It survived an International vacation, with all wheels intact. That is definitely a win in my book!Fast forward a few months later and I'm trying to find a 20" carry on suitcase. If it could be pink to match my other one, even better. I did some research and found out that my luggage is actually magenta (not pink). Amazon had them new for $65 and also had a "Used - Like New" one for about $35. I've had good success with products in the "Used - Like New" category before, so I thought why not. I am so glad that I did. The suitcase arrived in perfect condition.My favorite features are the wheels (they glide so smoothly in any direction, on any surface: carpet, hardwood, tile, concrete, etc) and the telescoping handle (it fully extends so you don't have to hunch over at all). The zippers work well; there's also one that allows for expansion. (Note if the suitcase is expanded, it may exceed the allowed carry-on size) The interior is pink with white polka-dot.I am very pleased with my purchase. (With my bargain hunting, I've gotten a matching set for under $50) I highly recommend this product.
